<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-01-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="316" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File 3714/1.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Persian Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Persia</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-09"><hi rend="italic">January 9,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Minister</hi>: I fulfill a very painful duty in
                            communicating to your excellency the sorrowful calamity that has
                            stricken the Persian nation in the decease of its beloved and regretted
                            sovereign Mozaffer-ed-Dine Shah.</p>
                        <p>Please accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morteza.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>